Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: pan
Version: 0.1.0
Summary: Command line tool with sane defaults for building academic articles from markdown using pandoc.
Home-page: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pan/
Author: Ben Whalley
Author-email: benwhalley@gmail.com
License: LICENSE.txt
Description: Pan: Command line tool with sane defaults for building academic articles from markdown using pandoc
        =======================================================================================================
        
        You will need to install pandoc first: http://johnmacfarlane.net/pandoc/installing.html
        
        
        Includes Stata features to build 'woven' documents with markdown, stata and LaTeX to pdf.
        
        
        
        Output formats
        ------------------
        
        rtf
        
        html
        
        plain
        
        pdf (default)
        
        
        
        
        Markdown header block options
        ------------------------------------
        
        
        XXX 
        
        
        
        
        Special classes for block elements
        ------------------------------------
        
        .stata .hide .run
        
        .instructor
        
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
